    "topic": ["Polynomials and Rational Functions"],
    "Question": {
      "content": "If P(x) = 8x³ + 22x² - x - 15 and q(x) = 2x + 5, then P(x)/q(x) is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "4x² + x - 3",
        "2x² + x - 4",
        "4x² - x - 3",
        "2x² - x - 4"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "4x² + x - 3"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='color: var(--explainColor); background: var(--explainBg); padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--strongColor);'>\n  <h4 style='color: var(--strongColor); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px;'>Polynomial Division</h4>\n  \n  <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>\n    <strong style='color: var(--strongColor);'>Step 1: Use Polynomial Long Division</strong><br>\n    Divide 8x³ + 22x² - x - 15 by 2x + 5\n  </div>\n\n  <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>\n    <strong style='color: var(--strongColor);'>Step 2: Perform Division</strong><br>\n    <div style='background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05); padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 8px 0;'>\n      8x³ ÷ 2x = 4x²<br>\n      4x² × (2x + 5) = 8x³ + 20x²<br>\n      Subtract: (22x² - 20x²) = 2x²<br>\n      Bring down: 2x² - x<br>\n      2x² ÷ 2x = x<br>\n      x × (2x + 5) = 2x² + 5x<br>\n      Subtract: (-x - 5x) = -6x<br>\n      Bring down: -6x - 15<br>\n      -6x ÷ 2x = -3<br>\n      -3 × (2x + 5) = -6x - 15<br>\n      Remainder: 0\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style='background: var(--cAnsBg); color: var(--cAns); padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; border-left: 4px solid var(--cAns); margin-top: 15px;'>\n    <strong>✓ Final Answer:</strong> P(x)/q(x) = 4x² + x - 3\n  </div>\n</div>"
    }
  },
