  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 27",
    "topic": ["Relations and Functions"],
    "Question": {
      "content": "When is a relation R, with an example, on a set said to be an equivalence relation?",
      "type": "subjective",
      "options": []
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "A relation R on set A is an equivalence relation if it is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive. Example: Equality relation on any set."
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='color: var(--explainColor); background: var(--explainBg); padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--strongColor);'>\n  <h4 style='color: var(--strongColor); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px;'>Equivalence Relation</h4>\n  \n  <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>\n    <strong style='color: var(--strongColor);'>Step 1: Three Required Properties</strong><br>\n    A relation R on set A is an equivalence relation if:<br>\n    • Reflexive: (a,a) ∈ R for all a ∈ A<br>\n    • Symmetric: If (a,b) ∈ R, then (b,a) ∈ R<br>\n    • Transitive: If (a,b) ∈ R and (b,c) ∈ R, then (a,c) ∈ R\n  </div>\n\n  <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>\n    <strong style='color: var(--strongColor);'>Step 2: Example - Equality Relation</strong><br>\n    On set A = {1,2,3}, R = {(1,1), (2,2), (3,3)}<br>\n    • Reflexive: Each element relates to itself<br>\n    • Symmetric: If a=b then b=a<br>\n    • Transitive: If a=b and b=c then a=c\n  </div>\n\n  <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>\n    <strong style='color: var(--strongColor);'>Step 3: Another Example</strong><br>\n    Congruence modulo n: a ≡ b (mod n) if (a-b) is divisible by n\n  </div>\n\n  <div style='background: var(--cAnsBg); color: var(--cAns); padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; border-left: 4px solid var(--cAns); margin-top: 15px;'>\n    <strong>✓ Final Answer:</strong> Reflexive, symmetric, transitive relation. Example: Equality.\n  </div>\n</div>"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
